<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Johnston, John. Description of the Country around Lakes Superior and Huron, 1809. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0018</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">and in fact a part of Canada<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Their line should at least have followed the Southern Shores of Lakes Huron and Micha<span class="DelHand-author">u</span>gan and from thence to the northern bank of the Mississipi<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  This should have been their ne plus Ultra, and would have Still given them Twenty Millions of Acres of the most fertile lands to which they had no claim, and of course would have been perfectly satisfyed with, until increasing strength should encourage them to new encroachments<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  But to return from a painful digression<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Rappids for properly speaking, it is not a fall, Runs over a bed of Red freestone interspersed with large whinstone and Rocks of coarse Granite<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The eddies formed around these Rocks are the best places for taking the Whitefis<span class="AddHand-editors">[h]</span> which is done with Scoop nets fixed to a pole bent So that the circle to which the net is attached can be brought to lie nearly flat on the bottom<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The man in the bow of the Canoe lets the net drop right over the fish and the Steersman lets the Canoe gently descend when the fisher gives his net a sudden turn and hauls it up close by the Canoe and then proceeds to push up against the stream to the same po<span class="AddHand-editors">[ol]</span> if he Sees any have escaped or else pushes off to another<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  As some of the pools are more frequente<span class="AddHand-editors">[d]</span> than Others by the fish you will see ten or a dozen Canoes Sometimes in a line waiting their turns</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[3]</span></p>

